annotation.TEXT: There's more of these fairies. They remind me of certain fairies from stage 4 of Touhou 6, which also clear out all on screen bullets upon their demise.
Okay, now I think those circling things up there that are spraying green bullets everywhere are invincible. Or, at least, I haven't been able to deal enough damage to kill them.
BGM: Ys Origin - Devil's Wind
Bah. I kind of let myself get cornered there. However, looking back, I saw an opening that I could've used to escape. Oh, well.
Wow, still not enough? I didn't release the fire button at all during that volley...
BGM: Ys Origin - Tension
Destroying the plane gives you a nice number of power items. However, get ready, because here comes another plane!
This spell card is quite similar to one of Yuka's attacks in Touhou 4. You might be able to get a large amount of graze quickly from the edge of the interior of the flower you're in, but it's risky.

And, with that, my power is now maxed out at 9.99 (if I bomb now, I'll drop to 8.99, regardless of any additional power items I collect). I don't know if there's any extra benefit to grabbing power items while already at max power. If there is, let me know.
One of those bullets came uncomfortably close to me.
For this spell card, dodge the stars, obviously.

...That wasn't enough to get the gauge back to the "F" mark, possibly because I released fire and focus for a moment to auto-collect stuff there. (The Statu gauge drains very quickly while you're not firing.)
Whoa, I managed to nicely slip right through those shots there!

Okay, now this particular fairy is interesting, because when she's defeated, all currently on screen bullets will be cancelled out. Also, you'll auto-collect any already on screen items when that happens, too.
Yeah, giant laser beams! They could be good for grazing, but I'm kind of too preoccupied with shooting and dodging other stuff to really take advantage of the graze potential here.
It goes down just as easily as the first one.
Oh, and she sprays knives behind her, but you're not dumb enough to go up there, right?
BGM: Ys Origin - Scars of the Divine Wing

Oh, man. Curvy lasers! When this spell starts, you actually want to get relatively close to Rumia. Not too close, obviously, but close enough so that you don't have to worry about the fast-moving lasers that go across the bottom of the screen.

Although I don't show it here, if you're at the very bottom of the screen when time stops, a few of the knives will fail to spawn, giving you a nice opening to go through at the top of the ring after they've reappeared and converged.
Oh, hey there, Sakuya! How's it going? So, here's the stage 3 midboss.
Nuts. I let some items drop. I thought I'd be able to defeat that bullet-cancelling fairy fast enough.
Hello, and welcome back to Touhoupachi Blissful Death! ...Whoops, I guess there were a few more lines of dialogue following the stage 2 boss. Well, whatever. Now let's start stage 3!
Whoa, man! Lasers! Well, I can graze these, but...

Wow, I practically "Icicle Fall -Easy-"-ed that one. However, sometimes you will have to do a little bit of dodging there. Okay, now for Rumia's final spell, and it's a survival spell that I have not successfully captured yet.
D'oh. That time, I think I would've destroyed the bullet-cancelling fairy in time, so I just gave up half of the points from many of those items for no reason.
I hate how hard it is to see the boss's life ring sometimes. Maybe having the classic life bar like in the Touhou games prior to Great Fairy Wars would've been better for this game...
D'oh. I didn't quite reach the "F" mark. Oh, well.
Whoa, that was close. Well, there's Reimu A's bomb. It's not overly flashy, but it works pretty well, I guess.
Okay, see those thin red lines? You can pass through them, but they'll become thick lasers after a few seconds.
Yeah, the cross RNG wasn't being too friendly to me there, so I decided to bomb.
I'm pretty sure this non-spell is similar to an official Touhou bullet pattern, but I can't think of which one it might be right now.
You quite done there, game? ...Good. Okay, let's move on to the boss fight.
BGM: ???
Whoa, that's a big plane! It's not too difficult to quickly destroy, though. Also, there's a timer up there showing 30 seconds for this, but it doesn't decrease for some reason.
Finally! Okay, now for the next pattern, DO NOT go near the left or right sides of the screen! ...Yep, giant laser beams again.
Fortunately, this is not too difficult, but I am on the easiest difficulty after all. It's probably really insane on the highest difficulties.
It'll take a while, but I will capture this spell card before time runs out. (Fortunately, this card's time limit is large.)
With that plane destroyed, Yumemi is defeated. Up next is stage 5, which I'll be showing next time! To be continued...

By the way, I think those fairies disappear after a certain amount of time if you don't kill them fast enough, and they don't cancel out bullets or give you a free auto-collect if they vanish on their own that way.
Demo count: 1
The second half of this stage consists entirely of these invincible enemies. Just concentrate on dodging the bullets.
There's an enemy that shoots red bullets too. Yay for Christmas colors, regardless of what time of year it currently is!

These enemies are easy enough to destroy and give decent amounts of power items. (From what I've read, small power items are worth 0.005 power (so it takes 2 to gain 0.01 power), and large ones are worth 0.05 power.)

For Yumemi's final spell card, she summons another plane. However, this one doesn't go down as easily as the first three, and its shots are faster and more difficult to dodge. Furthermore, Yumemi tosses knives at you as well.

As you can see, Sakuya will periodically stop time and surround you with knives that start off moving away from you and then disappear. However, they'll reappear coming back towards that point, so move away from that spot!

Yumemi fires aimed bullets at you while randomly spawning crosses all over the place. Try to stream the bullets, but be ready to move quickly out of the way if a cross appears on top of or in front of you.
Oh, hey! I think that's Rumia! But, why is she wielding a sword? Also, are those bat wings? So, is this her EX form? ...But I still see the ribbon on her head, so I don't know.
Bah. I was expecting her to go further to the left than that. Yeah, I bombed again at the last second, but that's still better than dying.
And now there's three of these fairies at once.

Alright, time for stage 4. Oh, hey. I was able to figure out what this BGM was, since it initially sounded familiar to me. Okay, now when the stage begins, DO NOT go near the left or right sides of the screen!
BGM: Salamander 2 - Stage 5, Loop 2 (Planet Ratis)
Lots of little fairies here, which my homing shot mostly makes quick work of.
After taking out those three planes, the actual boss of the stage shows up.

Rumia charges at your location and releases a bunch of bullets, and she also leaves these trails behind that restrict your movement. This seems unusually difficult for the easiest difficulty level, unless there's some trick to it that I haven't picked up on yet.
Nothing really too threatening about Yuka's non-spell here. Just be sure to go around the white bullet walls.

ARGH!!! Rumia didn't make a sudden movement to the right there like that last time I faced this non-spell! Well, there's my first death of this run. Upon dying, very large power items appear totalling 2.00 power (essentially giving you 2 more bombs, unless you hit the power cap).
ARGH! Stupid clip-death. I could've sworn my hitbox was far enough away from the cross that hit me...
Unfortunately, my Statu gauge has already drained below the "F" mark, and this first enemy here isn't going to provide me with anything decent to graze. Oh, well.
Rumia opens with a familiar-looking pattern, and then adds some lasers into the mix.
Remember Kappa's Pororoca, one of Nitori's spell cards from Mountain of Faith? This looks like the exact same thing.
Hey there, Yuka. How's it going?

But, there's a third plane, which is just as easy as the first two. (Maybe these planes are here just to give you a chance to get some power items, since there were otherwise no destroyable enemies in the second half of this stage.)
Definitely quite a bit of danmaku to dodge here.
Hey there, Yumemi. How's it going?
I suppose I could try to graze those bullets, but they won't amount to much.

I wonder how you'd battle this spell card without homing shots, though... Maybe you'd have to take any opportunities you can find to briefly dart underneath Yumemi to get off any shots you can on her.
Oh, well. I'll just launch a bomb to help me survive. If you do bomb, try to make sure you remove those trails during it.
And surprisingly, she uses a survival spell card here! So, you just have to last about 16 seconds here. If you do so without dying or bombing, you'll capture it and get the spell card bonus.

Now, I'm not sure what the intended method for defeating this spell card is, but I noticed that I'm relatively safe right where I currently am, and I can let Reimu's homing shots hit the boss from here.
Once the survival card ends, Sakuya gives you a 1-up (Thanks!) and then the background and music change for the second half of stage 3.

Ooh, this spell's good for graze, due to all of those aimed blue bullets, but you've gotta be careful not to overgraze (since filling the Statu gauge completely is deadly), and of course watch out for the other bullets.
Demo count: 2
Other fairies will come straight towards you, but I wouldn't worry, since your shots should take them out no problem before they reach you, even if you're not using a homing shot type.
Alright, that's it for Yuka.
